#: ../../../doc/en/example/parametrize.rst:579
msgid ""
"You'll see that we don't have an ``opt2`` module and thus the second test "
"run of our ``test_func1`` was skipped.  A few notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/parametrize.rst:582
msgid ""
"the fixture functions in the ``conftest.py`` file are \"session-scoped\" "
"because we don't need to import more than once"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/parametrize.rst:585
msgid ""
"if you have multiple test functions and a skipped import, you will see the "
"``[1]`` count increasing in the report"
