#: ../../../doc/en/example/parametrize.rst:594
msgid "Set marks or test ID for individual parametrized test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/parametrize.rst:596
msgid ""
"Use ``pytest.param`` to apply marks or set test ID to individual "
"parametrized test. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/parametrize.rst:599
msgid ""
"# content of test_pytest_param_example.py\n"
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.mark.parametrize(\n"
"    \"test_input,expected\",\n"
"    [\n"
"        (\"3+5\", 8),\n"
"        pytest.param(\"1+7\", 8, marks=pytest.mark.basic),\n"
"        pytest.param(\"2+4\", 6, marks=pytest.mark.basic, "
"id=\"basic_2+4\"),\n"
"        pytest.param(\n"
"            \"6*9\", 42, marks=[pytest.mark.basic, pytest.mark.xfail], "
"id=\"basic_6*9\"\n"
"        ),\n"
"    ],\n"
")\n"
"def test_eval(test_input, expected):\n"
"    assert eval(test_input) == expected"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/parametrize.rst:619
msgid ""
"In this example, we have 4 parametrized tests. Except for the first test, we "
"mark the rest three parametrized tests with the custom marker ``basic``, and "
"for the fourth test we also use the built-in mark ``xfail`` to indicate this "
"test is expected to fail. For explicitness, we set test ids for some tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/parametrize.rst:624
msgid ""
"Then run ``pytest`` with verbose mode and with only the ``basic`` marker:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/example/parametrize.rst:626
msgid ""
"$ pytest -v -m basic\n"
"=========================== test session starts "
"============================\n"
"platform linux -- Python 3.x.y, pytest-9.x.y, pluggy-1.x.y -- $PYTHON_PREFIX/"
"bin/python\n"
"cachedir: .pytest_cache\n"
"rootdir: /home/sweet/project\n"
"collecting ... collected 24 items / 21 deselected / 3 selected\n"
"\n"
"test_pytest_param_example.py::test_eval[1+7-8] PASSED                [ 33%]\n"
"test_pytest_param_example.py::test_eval[basic_2+4] PASSED            [ 66%]\n"
"test_pytest_param_example.py::test_eval[basic_6*9] XFAIL             [100%]\n"
"\n"
"=============== 2 passed, 21 deselected, 1 xfailed in 0.12s ================"
msgstr ""

